ant part in human life, they do not belong in the art of painting. Through this distinction, Gilson sheds new light on the evolution of modern painting. A magisterial work of scholarship by an acclaimed historian of philosophy, Painting and Reality features paintings from both classical and modern schools, and includes extended selections from the writings of Reynolds, Delacroix, Gris, Gill, and Ozenfant.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aPainting. 0aReality. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh  aAugustine, St. (Aurelius Augustinus).  aBach, Johann Sebastian.  aBeethoven, Ludwig van.  aBotticelli, Sandro.  aChrist on the Cross (Giovanetti), Pl.  aDasein.  aDeath of Procris, The (Piero di Cosimo).  aGilson, Etienne.  aGiovanetti, Matteo, Christ on the Cross, Pl.  aKeats, John.  aLalo, Charles.  aMaritain, Jacques.  aMarriage Feast at Cana (Veronese).  aMendelssohn-Bartholdy, Felix.  aMertoun: Earl of Ellesmere Collection, Pl.  aMichelangelo Buonarroti.  aMonteverdi, Claudio, Orfeo.  aOsborne, Harold.  aPaintings.  aPlato.  aPusey, Edward Bouverie.  aShakespeare, William.  aSkutella, Martin.  aSouriau, Étienne.  abecoming, and being.  aexistence, actual.  aliterature.  amusic.  aobject(s), forms of.  apoetry, and arts.  aspirit, creativity of.  athing, painting as a.  a“lost” pictures.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertThe A. W. Mellon Lectures in the Fine Arts eBook Packagez978311129290840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691251875?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691251875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691251875/original  a978-3-11-129290-8  The A. W. Mellon Lectures in the Fine Arts eBook Package  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EC